EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear Sir / Madam,

We recently received your notice to prove claim.

The reason that we have not filed a claim on the above-mentioned account is that it was statute barred as at the date of insolvency. 

As verified by the OSB, due to the statute of limitations having expired, the debt is not a claim provable in the insolvent estate and as a result does not fall within the debts impacted by the insolvency proceedings.  

Please note that while a creditor cannot initiate a legal proceeding for recovery of a debt if the applicable statute of limitations on such debt has expired, that does not operate to prohibit a creditor’s right to continue other collection activity as permitted in accordance with the applicable provincial legislative regime. We also note that the time period a creditor is permitted to report a debt on a consumer’s credit bureau in accordance with the applicable credit reporting act is different than the time period for commencing a legal action on a debt in most provinces.

Thank You,

Canaccede Insolvency Processing

